title: label obj.R_ADDRMIPSU defined and not used
body:
Please answer these questions before submitting your issue. Thanks!

1. What version of Go are you using (`go version`)?
go version go1.6.1 linux/mips64le

2. What operating system and processor architecture are you using (`go env`)?
GOARCH="mips64le"
GOBIN=""
GOEXE=""
GOHOSTARCH="mips64le"
GOHOSTOS="linux"
GOOS="linux"
GOPATH=""
GORACE=""
GOROOT="/root/ws/go-linux-mips64le-bootstrap"
GOTOOLDIR="/root/ws/go-linux-mips64le-bootstrap/pkg/tool/linux_mips64le"
GO15VENDOREXPERIMENT="1"
CC="gcc"
GOGCCFLAGS="-fPIC -fmessage-length=0"
CXX="g++"
CGO_ENABLED="0"

3. What did you do?
Cross compile a mips64le golang, and then use it to builld golang on fedora 23 mips64el.then report error.

4. What did you expect to see?
Compile OK, no error reported.

5. What did you see instead?
bootstrap/link/internal/mips64
# bootstrap/link/internal/mips64
/root/rpmbuild/BUILD/go/src/cmd/link/internal/mips64/asm.go:157[/root/rpmbuild/BUILD/go/pkg/bootstrap/src/bootstrap/link/internal/mips64/asm.go:160]: label obj.R_ADDRMIPSU defined and not used
bootstrap/link/internal/ppc64
bootstrap/link/internal/x86
go tool dist: FAILED: /usr/lib/golang/bin/go install -v bootstrap/...: exit status 2
